import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['open'] = pd.to_numeric(data['open'], errors='coerce')
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='open', kde=True)
    plt.axvline(data['open'].median(), color='red', label='Median: {:.2f}'.format(data['open'].median()))
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of opening prices?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    data = data.dropna()
    sns.lineplot(x='date', y='open', data=data, label='Open')
    sns.lineplot(x='date', y='close', data=data, label='Close')
    plt.title('What is the relationship between opening and closing prices?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='ret', kde=True)
    plt.axvline(data['ret'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f'Mean: {data["ret"].mean():.2f}')
    plt.axvline(data['ret'].median(), color='green', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f'Median: {data["ret"].median():.2f}')
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of returns on investment?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['signal'] = data['signal'].astype('category')
    chart = sns.boxplot(x='signal', y='ret', data=data)
    plt.title('What is the relationship between trading signal and returns?', wrap=True)
    chart.axhline(data['ret'].median(), color='red', label='Median: {:.2f}'.format(data['ret'].median()))
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(8,6))
    sns.boxplot(data=data[['high', 'low']], ax=ax)
    ax.set_title('What is the distribution of highest and lowest prices?')
    ax.set_xlabel('Price')
    ax.set_ylabel('Type')
    ax.axhline(y=data['high'].median(), color='r', linestyle='--', label=f'Median High: {data["high"].median():.2f}')
    ax.axhline(y=data['low'].median(), color='b', linestyle='--', label=f'Median Low: {data["low"].median():.2f}')
    ax.legend()
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
